claim: Flublok contains 3x the hemagglutinin (HA) antigen content of standard-dose flu vaccines, which has been linked to greater immunogenicity vs standard-dose flu vaccines.
explanation: Side-by-side schematic diagrams of influenza hemagglutinin (HA) showing the globular head and fibrous stem regions with illustrations of glycan structures attached. Panel a shows cleaved HA1/HA2 with complex polysialylated glycans, while panel b shows uncleaved HA0 with paucimannose glycans, including annotations of fusion peptide status and disulfide bonds. The figure illustrates structural and glycosylation differences of HA proteins but provides no information on antigen dosing or comparisons of HA content per vaccine dose. Therefore, it does not support the claim about Flublok containing 3× the HA antigen content. Note: Image quality is sufficient to identify content; no dosage or immunogenicity data are presented.
